<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Vertical centering with negative and positive top positioning</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#positioning-scheme"/>
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Equal 50% positive and negative positioning can vertically center objects."/>
        <style type="text/css">
            div, p
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
            .outer
            {
                background: green repeat-x center url('/w3ccss../support/swatch-red.png');
                width: 200px;
                height: 300px;
            }
            .inner
            {
                background: red;
                position: relative;
                top: 50%
            }
            .inner p
            {
                background: green;
                height: 15px;
                position: relative;
                top: -50%;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div class="outer">
            <div class="inner">
                <p></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>